  "prompt": "How do I save an answer on Quora?",
  "response": "To save an answer on Quora, you can use the \"Bookmark\" feature. Here are the steps to bookmark an answer:\n\n1. **Find the Answer**: Navigate to the answer you want to save.\n2. **Click on the Three Dots**: On the bottom right corner of the answer, you\u2019ll see three dots. Click on these dots to open a menu.\n3. **Select \"Bookmark\"**: In the menu, click on the \"Bookmark\" option. This will save the answer to your bookmarks.\n\nYou can access your bookmarked answers by clicking on your profile icon and selecting the \"Bookmarks\" section. This feature allows you to easily find and refer to saved answers whenever you need them.",
